# Created by venv; see https://docs.python.org/3/library/venv.html

In your terminal:

bash
rm -rf ~/.qwen
or, for some setups:

bash
rm -rf ~/.cache/qwen
This wipes the saved OAuth tokens and cached credentials.

If you want to be extra careful, you can run:

bash
ls -a ~ | grep qwen
to see if any qwen folders are present, then remove as above.


